summary: Didn’t you find the “don’t forget that [you’re our family” a bit threatening?? I’m worried there’s going to be problems now
question: Didn’t you find the “don’t forget that [you’re our family” a bit threatening?? I’m worried there’s going to be problems now
answer:
I didn’t see it as threatening at all.

Her words are in the exact same episode as Jon is dropped with the bombshell that he’s not Ned’s son. That sentence was about reminding Jon that he’ll always be part of their family, regardless of whether Ned’s his biological father or not. And it’s coming from the one person who always treated him like he belonged. Poetic, really.

D&D made it a point to mention this in their commentary. I don’t always agree with them, but they nailed that.

I guess you’re concerned about Arya going against Jon, but I doubt that very much. Arya defending Sansa wasn’t about her taking sides, because we’ve established in S7 that she’ll cut anyone that hurts Jon. It was a pretty massive issue between her and Sansa because of how loyal she is to him, and even Littlefinger played that to his advantage.

Jon and Sansa are on two sides atm. If they continue to be at conflict, the Starks are vulnerable to losing whatever power or security they’ve managed to scrap together. A divided family is a weak family, so they really can’t afford to be quarreling right now. Bran won’t get involved unless he’s telling everyone they’re morons for wasting time, after which everyone will just ignore him and continue wasting time and neither Jon nor Sansa seem inclined to change their mind.

That leaves Arya as the only one that can do something about it. She’s just come home and finally has her family together. She’s not going to let it fall apart again, and for that to happen, I imagine they’re setting her up as the mediator, because Jon and Sansa are more likely to listen to her than each other. It’s not really a role I want for her, sure, but she’s all about keeping her pack alive and strong.

Whatever drama we’re having to go through now will last one more episode before the devil himself decides to drop in for a house visit, so I’m just waiting this out lol
